Thanks to a very memorable patient and a keen sense of curiosity, Carolyn found herself not only a visitor of Arkham, but it's savior.
The beast's corpse dissolves before her eyes leaving a swampy mess. The streets are quiet once again.
Until the beast is no more. It lies limp on the ground. The creatures roaming the streets flee into their rapidly disappearing portals.
With energy to spare, Carolyn sinks her sword into the Shub-Niggurath for a final fatal time. It collapses to the ground, writhing slowly...
But after all the creatures she had defeated, she was prepared to battle for far longer than the beast could have imagined!
But the Shub-Niggurath continues to duck and dodge around her, moving like no physical being should be able to
Her experience is buying her lots of time as she continues to swing with her sword, hacking away bit by bit!
The Shub-Niggurath senses this is not her first encounter with a being from Another World. This psychologist may be a worthy opponent!
It is a giant mass of tentacles with many faces full of gnashing teeth. Carolyn grips her sword knowing it is her only chance to survive!
The streets are in utter pandimonium. Creatures are everywhere. Bodies are strewn across the land. And an ancient being like nothing seen...
She wakes to an empty hospital. She calls out, but only hears her own voice echo. She gets dressed and steps out into the streets...
Finally she has a clear path. She arrives and is admitted. Carolyn takes a well earned rest. #ArkhamHorror
Altho she is caught off guard, she still slays it with her trust magical sword. She really would like to be able to get to that Hospital now
But a Mi-Go sweeps down from the sky! She cannot escape and must fight!
She knows she can avoid most of them, but takes a swing at a Cultist and a Vampire since she's in the neighborhood. They both go down easily
Before she can make it the Hospital, she is interrupted by a swarm of creatures in the Misatonic University streets! #ArkhamHorror
On her way to the Hospital, she reads more of The King in Yellow. Suddenly it all makes sense! She realizes how imminent the danger truly is
The nearby Dock workers witness this, and Carolyn tells them of her adventure so far. They give her a few bucks and recommend the Hospital
A witch is sighted in the street. Sword in hand, Carolyn approaches. The witch lashes out but is no match for Carolyn and her sword!
A portal back home opens in the distance. She sprints thru it. It closes behind her, but there is no seal. This place still isn't safe...
She is knocked to the ground, but the creature is gone. She is hurt and shaken, but the battle seems to be over. #ArkhamHorror
The creatures finally clear, so Carolyn moves along. Out of nowhere a ghost like creatures appears in front of her, attacking with a sword!
There are monsters everywhere. This place is horrible! Carolyn hides, hoping they eventually move along.
In pure shock, Carolyn is knocked to the ground. The beast dives at her but she holds out her sword, impaling it before it strikes.
A snake-like beast slithers thru the air and attacks with his gaping mouth open, surrounded by outreached tentacles!
She is drawn into a shadowy Abyss where the full moon shines in distance, illuminating dark moving paths all around her.
Eyes still watering, Carolyn investigates what her map describes only as "Witch House" only to find an open portal! She steps thru.
She finds a chalkboard covered with insightful writings, but the dust sets off her allergies like crazy. Violent coughing fits ensues.
A nearby Science Building draws Carolyn's attention as a source of further knowledge. #ArkhamHorror
She waits until the sky clears once again. She sees police cars patroling in the distance. The gate finally closes behind her.
She returns to Arkham, but the sky is a different color. The portal behind her remains open!
She does, however, find a stray page on the ground. It tells her exactly where the portal exit is and how to best seal it. Perfect!
In the Halls she sees a giant book open up before her. A extremely intimidating guard stands nearby, and she thinks better of approaching.
Entering the portal she is taken to a place known as the Great Hall of Celeano.
Leaving the history records, still shaken by her findings, Carolyn spots another open portal in the distant woods. She investigates.
She starts digging thru old records, only to find a folder with her own family name on it. It's contents are horrifying. Could this be true?
Her map indicates a Historical Society across town. Perhaps this town has a documented history of strange occurrences. #ArkhamHorror
She swings her glorious mystic sword and the creature is slain!
She stumbles face first into giant formless snail-like creature of shifting shape. Its horrid and threatening!
Now that she's finally home, she can read this Cabala of Saboth text that she can finally make sense of. Her reading distracts her however..
Carolyn sees an open portal back home and sprints towards it. She arrives back at the Graveyard, the portal closing and sealing behind her.
Alright. back to this game... #ArkhamHorror #Sidetracked
Taking a moment to say that "Reapers" by @muse has the catchiest fucking guitar riffs ever. I keep playing it. God this songs rocks!

*consulting rule book*
Kate sees a portal back to Arkham in the distance... She heads towards it, eager to return home. Hoping there's still some of it left...
There are monsters lurking around every corner, so Kate is careful to sneak around them.
She is transported to The Great Hall of Celeano. The sky is dark and the feeling is ominous.
Seeing what may be one of her only opportunities, Kate runs thru the unguarded open portal! #ArkhamHorror
The congregation proceeds to slaughter all of the beasts dwelling around the open portal at the Historical Society. It is a sight to be seen
The church members are arming themselves when she arrives. "We're taking back this neighborhood. And we have God on our side!" One yells.
And while she may be a woman of science, desperate times call for desperate measures. Kate heads to the church to be blessed.
She tells of her trips to other dimensions. He introduces himself as John Legrasse. His presence is strong willed and brave. Your new ally.
Monsters are spilling out of open portals left and right. Kate cannot do this alone. At the nearby Boarding House she finds a survivor.
No solice is found. The ground shakes beneath Kate, knocking her off her feet. A bookshelf crashes around her. She is hurt, but will manage
There are creatures everywhere! Kate runs to the Silver Twilight Lodge once again, hoping to find safety with her new membership.
The cultist is slain and leaves behind an ancient book telling of Pharoahs and blood rituals to defeat ancient beings. Kate keeps the book.
Suddenly, a Cultist appears before Kate. However, this was a familiar one... she had faced this exact one earlier! And it was alive again!
No dog, but an old man is found. He begins to tell you a story. It is extremely long and rambling. In the end, it is nothing but nonsense.
Thoughts of that dog still haunt her. The woods continues to call her. And once again, Kate follows the call... #ArkhamHorror
Apparently this satisfied their needs, and she was granted membership. She always suspected these guys were kind of strange... #ArkhamHorror
In the city, she is chased by alien beasts, but escapes thru several alleys. She arrives back in the Silver Twilight Lodge, perplexed.
She is greeted by Carl. He offers her membership, in exchange for a favor. Kate agrees, and a portal to the City of the Great Race opens!
The Silver Twilight Lodge. It's always been a secretive place. Maybe some of it's members are still around. Hiding in their mansion.
She fights off another Cultist - do they ever STOP? - and catches her breath in the French Hill streets.
The gate seals behind her and the Witch House is safe, but Kate can tell that Arkham has gotten worse since she left... is anybody left?
At the end of this hallway theres an open portal back home. Kate runs thru it, arriving across town from where she left. At the Witch House!
It's an ancient Flesh Ward spell. Could come in handy against a strong creature if needed...
Feeling confident in her detection of a pattern, Kate swipes the scroll while the eye is closed and darts down the nearest hallway!
The eye blinks, slowly. Remains shut for a moment, then slowly reopens. Kate freezes in place, watching the eye blink.
The comes upon an alter with a scroll resting upon it. A gigantic eye peeks thru the wall behind it, staring directly at the scroll.
She looks behind her to see a shadow of Earth... her hometown of Arkham... familiar. Safe. This comforts her, knowing she will return.
Kate is in a maze of mile-high living walls. She can see creatures slithering around in them. Faces looking out at her. Teeth gnashing.
Eerie piano music is heard in the background as she literally travels to Another Dimension.
It beings to pour rain. There's no use in standing around. Kate spots an open portal at the Unvisited Isle, and heads into it. #ArkhamHorror
She passes by the Unnamed old abandoned house once again. Her flux stabilizer starts humming. She knows she's safe.
She returns to the science lab. Speaks to an old colleague of the various monsters she's fought. The colleague shares what they've heard too
The city is nearly abandoned. Most have fled out of fear. Shops everywhere are boarded up.
Extremely disappointed by her inability to catch a goddamn dog, she seeks solace in the place she is most familiar. The science building.
She tried. She tried so hard. She really did. But she is completely spent. The dog is gone. Stupid. Fucking. Dog.
Against all odds, Kate sees the dog again! She races towards it and it immediately bolts in the other direction! STUPID FUCKING DOG!
Along the way she is startled by a zombie in the Uptown Streets. Her axe slays it, along with a nearby Cultist.
Kate thinks of that dog from the woods. In the midst of all this chaos, the dog seems to worry her most. Maybe one more trip to the woods...
Once up close, Kate is much more fearful of this Ghoul. Her axe, however, is not. One more dead Ghoul.
In the nearby Northside neighborhood, Kate spots another Ghoul. Northside is usually such a nice neighborhood. Time to make it safe again!
The gate is sealed up behind her. Independence Square is now safe.
In the distance Kate sees an open portal, returning to Arkham. She runs for towards it.
She is fine... but feeling confused. She realizes she can no longer remember one of her spells. It's gone from her mind completely...
The city is mostly abandoned. She see's the carcass of an alien creature but moves on. Suddenly a ripple through the air knocks her down.
Kate is teleported to an acient city. The City of the Great Race as it is mentioned in her research. Never thought she'd see it for herself.
Just as she had suspected, a portal is open over Independence Square, only a few blocks away. It's time to close this down!
the Historical Society is all the way across town. And her Flux Stabalizers is starting to give off signs of something closer...
A man suddenly runs in, exhausted. "Another one of those portal things just opened up over the Historical Society!" They just keep coming...
Its full of research papers. Dark supernatural stuff. Just like what she had been studying. Could prove useful. She pays him the money.
She sits at a table. Joey "the Rat" Vigil quickly joins her. He slides her a file... $2 is what he asks for it. #ArkhamHorror
Kate decides to see what she can find out from the locals. Hibbs Roadhouse isn't always the safest joint, but she thinks it may have insight
Kate hears approaching sound. Sirens. Several cars and trucks with FBI painted on the side speed by. In the distance, gunshots are heard.
Kate revisits the old abandoned house to seek more clues. She finds safety with the elder sign, but little else.
Kate is scared, but still fights for her life, axe in hand. The creature is slain.
It scowls at Kate and begins to walk towards her.
Leaving the general store, Kate sees a giant hairless brute shambling about the streets, flickering in and out of existence within Arkham
Among the goods, Kate sees what she needs most. Some freakin TNT. She buys the dynamite for $4.
Her axe has treated her well so far, but Kate feels like she could still use more equipment. Time to visit the General Store. #ArkhamHorror
Right as she approaches the entrance of the cave, a Cultist appears from the darkness. It attacks and she strikes it down with her axe.
Off to explore the Black Cave. Maybe some more clues will be found over there. #ArkhamHorror
Before leaving the old house, Kate sees an item in the fireplace... suddenly it ignites! She reaches for it but is burned. The item is gone.

The cultist notices Kate, finally. The robed figure charges while Kate readies her axe.
Her flux stabilizer lights up and emits a deep mechanical hum. The wind lessens. The elder sign glows less brightly. The portal remains shut
Suddenly the ground around her rumbles. The elder sign glows brightly. The wind swirls around her as another portal tries to open!

The slumbering Yog Sothoth makes it more difficult, but the portal closes and seals shut with an Elder Sign symbol burnt in the ground.
A pathway back to the unnamable abandoned house appears before her. Kate returns to Arkham. A cultist is nearby. She works quietly...
Kate sees a grate implanted into the side of a rock. She tries to pry it open, but it won't budge. She moves on.
With a one-handed swing, Kate sinks her axe into the Ghoul. It is swiftly defeated. Timid but deadly Kate Winthrop hardly breaks a sweat.
Out of nowhere a Ghoul appears! There is no escaping, Kate must fight for her life!

an open portal to another dimension is on the old abandoned house, with no creatures in sight. We must try to close this. Kate steps thru...
